					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Say your in bank 1 at $8342. When you switch to bank 2, would the PC still be at $8342?</div>
<br />Yes. The program counter is a register internal to the CPU, which doesn't know nor care about banks. For an example of code that exploits this fact heavily, see <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=5919#5919" class="postlink">The Wonderful World of NES/Fami Cart Copy Protection</a>.</div>

